<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested two men on Friday who are
wanted by the U.S. authorities in connection with a drug syndicate
that smuggled heroin into the United States in the bodies of dead
fish, authorities said.
   A police statement said the two men _ a Chinese and a
Chinese-American _ were arrested at their homes in this British
colony.
   The two, whose names were not released, will appear before a
magistrate on Saturday for extradition proceedings, the statement
said.
   Authorities arrested 11 alleged members of the syndicate after
police in Shanghai on March 9 found eight pounds of heroin stuffed
in packets and sewn into the bodies of dozens of fish. The heroin
was found in 25 boxes of fish that were to be flown to San
Francisco by China's national airline, CAAC.
   The 11 people arrested in connection with the heroin seizure
included six apprehended in China, three in the United States and
two in Hong Kong.
