<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, saying he won't tolerate another Pentagon
procurement scandal under his administration: ``We're not going to
surrender our national security to greed and corruption. We're not
going to use our defense dollars to line the pockets of Washington
consultants.''
   
   LLOYD BENTSEN, giving Bush credit for unveiling a $2.2 billion
day care proposal earlier this week: ``I think the Bush proposal is
a step in the right direction and I'm delighted to see them get
aboard on this issue.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, saying he won't divulge his choice of a running
mate until the Republicans convene in New Orleans: ``I will keep my
own counsel.''
   
   MARLIN FITZWATER, presidential spokesman, correcting a statement
by visiting West German leader Franz Joseph Strauss that American
policy will stay the same regardless of who wins the presidential
election: ``He (Dukakis) is basically for a weaker defense and
cutting defense, and we are for a strong defense. He is for
reducing commitments all around the world, it would seem.''
