<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market advanced broadly today as fears
of higher interest rates abated and a vibrant technical rally took
hold.
   Analysts said much of the day's gains reflected fresh strength
in the credit markets, where bond prices rose and interest rates
declined.
   Stock prices opened higher and advanced in a measured manner
throughout the session. Analysts said computer-triggered buy
programs helped boost the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials
beyond the 2,100 mark, a key pscyhological barrier, at about midday.
   With the Dow firmly above that level, institutional investors,
believing that a foundation had been built for a further advance,
left the sidelines in search of equities, said Philip Puccio, a
senior vice president at Dillon, Read & Co.
   Analysts said that as long a the bond market holds onto its
gains, there is an incentive for the stock market's summer rally to
resume.
